{
  "texts": [
    "For tree-based models, these methods take into account the inherent structured nature of programs and parse them into a tree such as an Abstract Syntax Tree (AST).",
    "For example, Yin et al. [164] train an LSTM to generate a sequence of tree-construction actions and subsequently build the AST from these actions.",
    "Rabinovich et al. [121] propose the Abstract Syntax Networks and directly generate the tree structure of source code.",
    "Another work [133] design Transformer blocks to encode both the natural language and the previously generated grammar rules and then predict subsequent grammar rules in the sequence.",
    "In recent years, the advent of pre-trained models [30,146] has achieved significant improvement in the field."
  ]
}